  "text": "The authoritative source of the error 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' originates in the upstream etcd-io/etcd repository, specifically in two files within the mvcc (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) storage layer. The error variable ErrCompacted is defined in server/mvcc/kvstore.go (line 39) as: `var ErrCompacted = errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\")`. This error is returned by the rangeKeys function in server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go (line 128), which is responsible for reading key ranges from the etcd store. The rangeKeys function checks if the requested revision (rev) is less than the compactMainRev (line 136-137), and if so, returns the ErrCompacted error. This occurs when a client requests a revision that has been garbage-collected by etcd's automatic compaction mechanism. The kubernetes/kubernetes repository contains vendored copies of these files under vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/server/v3/mvcc/kvstore.go and kvstore_txn.go, but these are NOT the authoritative source—they are merely copies of the upstream etcd code frozen at a specific version. The Kubernetes apiserver has its own error-mapping layer at staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/errors.go that translates this etcd error into Kubernetes error types (ResourceExpired), but this is also not the authoritative source; it only maps the error that originates from etcd. For bug reporting purposes, the issue should be filed against the etcd-io/etcd repository."
}
